procedure: Replace Blue Filter Behind Intake Vents
procedureDetails:
Open door and replace filter that covers the 3 intake vents at the bottom of the door.


Filter size: 6" x 18"


Note: The filter on these units has been modified by Vector due to the OEM parts being too fragile and unmaintainable. Remove black plastic guards on the outside of the unit that are damaged or coated with sticky lint. They are not needed with filter on the inside.

Wipe down bulbs using isopropyl alcohol and a lint-free rag.

 

 

Wear lint-free gloves when touching bulbs! Skin oil can create hot spots and shorten the lifespan of the bulb

Organize area and replace drum as necessary
procedureDetails:
Organize area:

  • Remove empty drums and place in common area. Be sure to include drum lid and hardware.

  • Remove empty pallets

Replace drum:

  1. Remove new drum from pallet

  2. Lift plunger on machine

  3. Remove all pressure from machine

  4. Remove empty drum from machine

  5. Use drum dolly to add new drum

  6. Safely insert plunger into drum and add pressure

  7. Discard empty pallet
